
EMPATHY		SOURCEPAGE:p.7	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You have learned to experience emotion.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cha 13, android.	PRERACE:1,Android	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13	BENEFIT:You lose the emotionless racial trait. You can gain morale bonuses, and can be affected by emotion-based effects and fear effects. You lack the +4 racial bonus on saving throws against mind-affecting effects.	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Empathy
EXTRA SURGE		SOURCEPAGE:p.7	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You can use your nanite surge ability more often than normal.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Con 13, nanite surge racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Nanite Surge	PRESTAT:1,CON=13	BENEFIT:You can use your nanite surge ability one additional time per day. Special: You can take Extra Surge multiple times. Its effects stack.	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	STACK:YES	MULT:YES	BONUS:VAR|NaniteSurgeTimes|1
NANITE DISRUPTION	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You can use your nanite surge to inflict wounds upon other mechanical beings.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Nanite surge racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Nanite Surge	BENEFIT:As long as you are adjacent to an android, a robot, or a creature primarily made of electronic components (GM's discretion), you can use your nanite surge ability as an immediate action to short-circuit that creature's hardware. If you succeed at a melee touch attack and the target fails a Will save (DC = 10 + 1/2 your character level + 1/2 your Constitution modifier), it takes a penalty equal to 1 + 1/2 your level (minimum 0) on its next d10 roll. This penalty lasts until the beginning of your next turn.
RAPID RECOVERY	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:When you heal damage with your nanite surge, you also remove harmful effects.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Con 13, Rapid Repair, nanite surge racial trait.	PRESTAT:1,CON=13	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Nanite Surge	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Feat,Rapid Repair	BENEFIT:When you heal damage using Rapid Repair, you remove any and all of the following conditions: blinded, confused, dazzled, deafened, shaken, sickened, and staggered. You cannot cure blindness or deafness caused by loss of sensory organs.
RAPID REPAIR	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You can use your nanite surge to repair hit point damage.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Wis 13, nanite surge racial trait.	PRESTAT:1,WIS=13	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Nanite Surge	BENEFIT:You can use your nanite surge racial trait to heal a number of hit points equal to your character level, instead of its usual effects.

# Astronomical Feats
ASTROLOGICAL TIMING	SOURCEPAGE:p.27	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Astronomical	DESC:You can perform more accurate auguries according to planetary movements in relation to the Cosmic Caravan.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast augury as a spell or spelllike ability.	BENEFIT:You can use a cosmogram or star chart as an optional focus component for augury. When you do, the augury can account for consequences up to 1 hour into the future, and your chance of a successful reading increases by 4%%. If you also consult a calculating standard orrery or calculating grand orrery, the augury can see up to 1 day into the future and your chance of success increases by 8%%.
CELESTIAL GUIDANCE	SOURCEPAGE:p.27	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Astronomical	DESC:You can use the movements of the sun, moon, stars, and planets to navigate and acquire eldritch knowledge about the fundamental nature of reality.	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on Knowledge (geography) skill checks to learn about the stars or planets. At night, as long as the sky is clear and you can see the stars, you cannot get lost. Once per night when the stars are visible, you can reroll a Knowledge check you failed earlier in the day. When you do so, you can choose to roll the appropriate Knowledge skill check again or you can instead use your Knowledge (geography) skill to gain the same information.

